'''George James Meldon''' (born [[18 January]] [[1885]] in [[Dublin]], [[Ireland]]; died [[27 November]] [[1951]] in [[Worcestershire]], [[England]]) was an Irish [[cricket]]er. He was a right-handed batsman.

He made his debut for [[Irish cricket team|Ireland]] against [[Cambridge University Cricket Club|Cambridge University]] in July 1904, and went onto play for them twelve times, his last game coming in August 1912 against [[Scottish cricket team|Scotland]]. Nine of his Ireland games had [[first-class cricket|first-class]] status, and he also played one first-class match for Woodbrook Club and Ground against [[South African cricket team|South Africa]] in 1912.

